\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 12. P. egaliksensis} Wormsk. in Hornem.,{\i  Fl. Dan.}{\b  9}({\b 26}): 4 (1816). Efarinose; homostylous. Leaves 0·5-5 × 0·2-1·5 cm, elliptical to oblong-ovate, entire or obscurely denticulate, glabrous; lamina more or less abruptly contracted into petiole. Scape 1-15 cm, 1- to 9-flowered. Bracts 3-7 mm, subulate, gibbous at the base. Pedicels 1-3 times as long as bracts. Calyx 4-6 mm; teeth often glandular-ciliolate. Corolla 5(-9) mm in diameter, white or lilac; tube slightly longer than calyx. Capsule 5-10 mm, narrowly cylindrical, 1½-2 times as long as calyx.{\i  Moist pastures near the sea. N. Iceland}. Is. ({\i Greenland, Canada, Alaska}.)
\par 

